\int_{\Bbb{R}} f(x)\hat{g}(x)dx = \int_{\Bbb{R}} \hat{f}(y)g(y) dy.
f,g
A
|f(x)| \leq \frac{A}{1+x^2}
g
H(x,y):=f(x)g(y)e^{-ixy}
|H(x,y)|\leq \frac{A^2}{(1+x^2)(1+y^2)}
H
\mathbb R^2
\int_{\Bbb R}f(x)\widehat g(x)dx=\int_{\Bbb R^2}f(x)g(y)e^{-ixy}dydx=\int_{\Bbb R^2}f(x)e^{-ixy}g(y)dxdy=\int_{\Bbb R}\widehat f(y) g(y)dy.
